Three black workers were killed andseven injured in fighting at a South African zinc refinery lastnight, Gold Fields of South Africa Ltd said.    The company said two groups of workers began attacking eachother at about 1000 local time with machetes, knives and sticksat a hostel at the Zincor plant, some 40 kms east ofJohannesburg.    It said the fighting was "quelled" after 25 minutes by itsown security staff. Police were called but the fighting hadended by the time they arrived.    A company spokesman said he had no idea of the cause of thefighting. An investigation was underway, he said. Reuter&#3;